*ES0089.1*
February 10, 2026
ENGROSSED
SENATE BILL No. 89
_____
DIGEST OF SB 89 (Updated February 10, 2026 9:02 am - DI 140)
Citations Affected: IC 7.1-3.
Synopsis: Three-way permits. Provides the alcohol and tobacco
commission may issue not more than: (1) three new three-way permits
to the town of Schererville; (2) three new three-way permits to the city
of Lafayette; (3) two new three-way permits to the city of West
Lafayette; (4) eight new three-way permits to restaurants located within
a transit development district located in the city of Michigan City; (5)
two new three-way permits to the city of Delphi; and (6) two new three-
way permits to the city of Bloomington.
Effective: Upon passage.
Dernulc, Niemeyer, Niezgodski,
Spencer, Jackson L
(HOUSE SPONSORS — VANNATTER, O'BRIEN, OLTHOFF)
December 9, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Policy.
January 22, 2026, amended, reported favorably — Do Pass.
January 26, 2026, read second time, amended, ordered engrossed.
January 27, 2026, engrossed. Read third time, passed. Yeas 39, nays 6.
HOUSE ACTION
January 29, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Policy.
February 10, 2026, reported — Do Pass.
